items.title: Rain delays start of Twins-Yankees in Bronx
items.summary: The start of Tuesday's game between the Twins and the Yankees at Yankee Stadium has been delayed due to inclement weather. No estimated start time has been provided.
items.content: The start of Tuesday's game between the Twins and the Yankees at Yankee Stadium has been delayed due to inclement weather. No estimated start time has been provided.

items.title: Ferrell feels OK, lucky after taking liner to head
items.summary: A look at Jeff Ferrell on Tuesday would hardly reveal the trauma the Tigers reliever went through on the mound Monday night from a line drive off his head.
items.content: A look at Jeff Ferrell on Tuesday would hardly reveal the trauma the Tigers reliever went through on the mound Monday night from a line drive off his head.

items.title: Dodgers want more quality ABs from Grandal
items.summary: An All-Star in his first season with the Dodgers and the unquestioned starting catcher in his second year, Yasmani Grandal, now in his third season with the club, is battling a slump that jeopardizes his playing time in the postseason.

items.title: Hats on: Neris will continue to wear filthy cap
items.summary: Phillies closer Hector Neris has a filthy baseball cap. He knows this, but Neris said before Tuesday night's game against the Dodgers that he has no plans to clean the old one or use a new one.
